I think there's a different underlying problem here. The function starts with
	if (!media->sdes_in.length)
		return;

So media->sdes_in.head == NULL later on should never happen. The only way this can happen is due to a missing lock somewhere, and a race condition. Can you explain the circumstances in which you see this segfault?

